  "identifier": "AugspurgerIndex",
  "name": "AugspurgerIndex",
  "description": "An R package with a single function, augs_synchrony(), that calculates Augspurger's Index of Synchrony (Augspurger 1983, modified from Primack 1980) -- a phenology metric quantifying how much the flowering, or other phenological, periods of individuals in a population overlap in time. Operates on rectangular (tidy) data frames, handles multi-year data including leap years, and supports arbitrary grouping variables.",
